ight of Ak’Anon. We the gnomes have regarded you as a traitor and an accomplice to your brother. You shall be put to death once we find you! You cannot hide from us; there is no place in all of Norrath in which you can conceal your petty halfling arse. Are you just going to leave while your brother is executed right in front of hundreds of gnomes tomorrow? I think not. I suggest not interfering in your brother’s process of extermination, for you shall not be treated as well as he was!&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Tibith chuckled as he watched the stupid gnome yell out into the horizon. Sure his brother Les was to be put to death tomorrow for a crime he didn’t commit, but the young halfling still found it funny that the forces of Ak’Anon had yet to catch him. He had recently escaped  from a horrible jail cell in the depths of Ak’Anon after he and his brother had been charged with murder. They were accused of  assassinating the high wizard Korick Hofoldorf. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp His brother was not so lucky when he tried to break from the city. The guards were on their tail and they couldn’t seem to outrun them. Les had tried to duck behind a boulder as the guards ran by but one certain warrior saw him. The gnomes jumped on Les and beat him down with clubs until he was rendered unconscience. Tibith had managed to escape while the guards beat down his brother.  Tibith’s purpose was to now save his brother from the clutches of gnomes who knew not what the truth was.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Tibith and Les were traveling on a quest from Rivervale with an intent to see all the cities of Norrath. They had decided that they wanted to visit the great continent of Faydwer first and then make their way back. After they had visited Kaladim, Kelethin, and Felwithe, they set their sites on Ak’Anon. They had heard many rumors of the grand city of clockworks and knew that they would not have many chances to see such a site. While on their way to the city they were passing by the large windmills in the hills of Steamfont. They decided they would go inside one and ask one of the residents about the history of the grand structures. They walked quietly inside and tapped on the door to let their presence known.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hello???&quot; Tibith called, &quot;Anyone home??&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp No Answer. Once again they called out. This time, however, there was a different result.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ahhhggggg!!&quot; they heard a gurgling scream come from above. The two halflings scampered upstairs to see what the commotion was. The site they saw was a gruesome one. A horrible looking inkie stood over the bloody body a gnome cloaked in a beautiful looking blue robe. The halflings were stunned.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The dark elf looked up and growled. He quickly darted across to Les and Tibith,  smearing their hands and clothes with blood. The brothers watched as the evil being jumped out a window and into the hills. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Wha…what just happened?? &quot; Tibith whispered.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;HALT! What is going on here??&quot; a gnome guard shouted. &quot;High wizard Korick dead??? You two drop your weapons and back away. I charge you in the name of Ak’Anon. You shall pay for this!!&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The brothers were bound and hauled away without even being given a chance to explain themselves. There was a trial in which the halflings were declared traitors to the gnome race. Since they were both rogues in nature they were easily not liked by the citizens of Ak’Anon.  They were sentenced to death within an hour. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp After Tibith has escaped he took refuge in Steamfont. The city guards had searched for days for the elusive young rogue but had yet to find him. Many times they had come close to getting him but each time he got away. Now Tibith was planning on rescuing his brother tomorrow at the execution. He knew not how the gnomes planned on taking Les’ life, but it would not be pretty. Tibith went forth to check out the situation.<br>
