A drumrole began. Tibith reacted quickly; snatching a few throwing daggers out of his satchel he began to run towards the gaurds. A shout from the crowd made just about every gnome head turn in Tibith’s direction, even Les looked. Tibith froze, he knew he was done for. Suddenly the blood in his veins began moving and he started to get his senses back. He ran a few more paces and let fly his first dagger. It struck the first gnome warrior right in the eye; the warrior fell back with a sickening thud. Another dagger flew and another warrior fell. Gnomes everywhere were screaming with panic. The King began to issue out orders to his troops.<br>
&quot;Get him! It’s only one puny halfling! He cannot take out the great might of Ak’Anon!!&quot;<br>
Tibith heard the screams of the king. His mind went blank. He looked over at Les, his face was a look of horror. The final warrior stood in the path of Tibith. Tibith readied his final throwing dagger, he let it soar at the warrior. The gnome was quick though; he dodged nimbly to the side and let the dagger fly past; right into Les’ neck. Les died with a gurgling scream. The commotion stopped.. Tibith didn’t know what to do. He had slain his brother, his brother was dead. He immediately fled from the site and made his way back to his home of Rivervale. The gnomes decided not to give chase, as they had got what they wanted. The king did vow, however, that is that halfling ever returned he would slain on the spot.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uarcck.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arc CK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/6/00 4:18:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> Tibith sobbed uncontrollably  as he ran through the dark forest of Faydark. What was he going to do? His brother was dead and HE had killed him. How would explain to his parents what had happened? He stopped next to a grand oak tree, panting and crying. He looked at his surroundings. Everywhere he looked there were trees, trees and more trees. Greater Faydark was such a beautiful place. He decided that he would stop at Kelethin , city in the trees, and then make his way back to his homeland. He knew he must tell his parents all that has happened since they left almost three months ago.<br>
 He pulled off his satchel and dug through the contents. He quickly found what he was looking for, food. He hadn’t eaten all day and he was starving. He sat eating and thinking about his brother. He choked back tears while he choked down his food. He took a swig of water to wash and down and then he put all of his things back into the satchel. He threw it on his back and set off for Kelethin.<br>
<br>
<br>
It didn’t take long for Tibith to reach the city of Kelethin, home of the wood elves and a few half-elves. Tibith loved the city among the trees. The lift ride was always fun and most of the residents were fairly kind. He always had to be on the lookout for Orcs though, as they could pop up just about anywhere. He walked around a bit and then stopped in a shop to load up on supplies. He hadn’t planned on staying long in the city so he hurried over to the lift and took it down. He was about to rush off when he heard someone call out to him.<br>
&quot;Hey mate, where ya heading in such a hurry? Off to help slay some of those disgusting greenies eh?&quot;<br>
Tibith looked around for the caller of the voice. He saw a wood elf sitting near one of the lifts. The wood elf was glorious looking. He was dressed in a magnificent blue armor and carried a perilous looking sword accompanied by a dagger. Tibith replied a little nervously.<br>
&quot;Uhh…I was just returning to my homeland Rivervale, sir.&quot; <br>
&quot;Rivervale eh? Well I was thinking of heading to Qeynos. You look kind of lonely, mind if I join ya for the trip?&quot; the wood elf stood up and shouldered his backpack.<br>
Tibith replied with excitement, &quot;I’d mighty obliged if you did sir! I sure do hate to travel alone. My name is Tibith.&quot;<br>
&quot;Frishock Julesetter here, but ya can call me Frish&quot; he replied.<br>
&quot;Please to meet ya Frish, shall we make out departure?&quot; Tibith readied himself.<br>
&quot;One sec little sir,&quot; Frish pulled out a very nice looking mandoline and began to play. He started to chant some curious sounding words that Tibith couldn’t understand. Soon a blue light began to encircle the two. Tibith felt his legs tighten a bit. They soon loosened out and felt so much lighter.<br>
&quot;What did you do to me???&quot; Tibith questioned.<br>
&quot;Hehe, it’ll just loosen your legs a little, boy. Lets get moving. Oh by the way, if you don’t like to travel alone, why are you out here all by yourself?&quot; Frish questioned.<br>
Tibith related his tale to Frish as the two set out into the depths of Faydark. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/udrakc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drakc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/00 11:01:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> Not a bad story, do keep writing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showMessage?topicID=398.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showMessage?topicID=44.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.emailToFriend?topicID=449.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.threadControl?topicID=449.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=449.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=449.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><